# API Documentation — AD User Creator
**Base URL (dev):** `http://localhost:8080`  
**Frontend:** `http://localhost:5173`  
**Swagger UI (interactive):** `http://localhost:8080/docs`

---

## Route Groups

| Prefix | Description |
|---|---|
| `/api/ad` | Active Directory status and config |
| `/api/users` | Validate, analyze, create users |
| `/api/ai` | Gemini AI chat |

---

## 1. AD Info Routes

### `GET /api/ad/status`
Check if AD server is reachable and credentials are valid.

**PowerShell test:**
```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://localhost:8080/api/ad/status" -Method GET
```

**Expected response (dry run):**
```json
{
  "connected": true,
  "server": "192.168.1.10",
  "domain": "company.com",
  "dry_run": true,
  "message": "DRY RUN mode — not actually connecting to AD"
}
```

---

### `GET /api/ad/ous`
Fetch list of Organizational Units (mock list in dry run mode).

**PowerShell test:**
```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://localhost:8080/api/ad/ous" -Method GET
```

**Expected response:**
```json
{
  "ous": [
    { "name": "IT Department", "dn": "OU=IT,DC=company,DC=com", "description": "IT Staff" },
    { "name": "HR Department", "dn": "OU=HR,DC=company,DC=com", "description": "Human Resources" },
    { "name": "Finance",       "dn": "OU=Finance,DC=company,DC=com", "description": "Finance Team" }
  ],
  "count": 5
}
```

---

### `GET /api/ad/config`
Returns non-sensitive config info (no passwords exposed).

**PowerShell test:**
```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://localhost:8080/api/ad/config" -Method GET
```

**Expected response:**
```json
{
  "domain": "company.com",
  "server": "192.168.1.10",
  "base_dn": "DC=company,DC=com",
  "dry_run": true,
  "use_tls": false,
  "port": 389,
  "username_format": "firstname.lastname"
}
```

---

## 2. User Routes

### `POST /api/users/validate`
**Step 1** — Fast code-only validation. No AI, no AD call.  
Returns errors, warnings, and auto-generated fields.

**PowerShell test (minimal valid):**
```powershell
$body = @{
    first_name = "Jane"
    last_name  = "Doe"
    password   = "Welcome@123"
    ou_path    = "OU=IT,DC=company,DC=com"
} | ConvertTo-Json

Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://localhost:8080/api/users/validate" `
  -Method POST -ContentType "application/json" -Body $body
```

**Expected response (valid):**
```json
{
  "is_valid": true,
  "errors": [],
  "warnings": [],
  "auto_generated": {
    "username": "jane.doe",
    "display_name": "Jane Doe",
    "user_principal_name": "jane.doe@company.com"
  }
}
```

**Test: missing password special character:**
```powershell
$body = @{
    first_name = "Jane"
    last_name  = "Doe"
    password   = "Welcome123"
    ou_path    = "OU=IT,DC=company,DC=com"
} | ConvertTo-Json

Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://localhost:8080/api/users/validate" `
  -Method POST -ContentType "application/json" -Body $body
```

**Expected (invalid):**
```json
{
  "is_valid": false,
  "errors": ["Password must contain at least one special character (!@#$%&*...)"],
  "warnings": [],
  "auto_generated": { "username": "jane.doe", ... }
}
```

---

### `POST /api/users/analyze`
**Step 2** — After validation passes, get AI-generated (or fallback) summary for confirmation screen.

**PowerShell test:**
```powershell
$body = @{
    first_name  = "Jane"
    last_name   = "Doe"
    password    = "Welcome@123"
    ou_path     = "OU=IT,DC=company,DC=com"
    email       = "jane.doe@company.com"
    department  = "Information Technology"
    job_title   = "Software Engineer"
} | ConvertTo-Json

Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://localhost:8080/api/users/analyze" `
  -Method POST -ContentType "application/json" -Body $body
```

**Expected response:**
```json
{
  "validation": { "is_valid": true, "errors": [], "warnings": [...] },
  "analysis": {
    "summary": "You are about to create an AD user account for Jane Doe...",
    "details": ["Username: jane.doe", "UPN: jane.doe@company.com", ...],
    "warnings": [],
    "confirmation_prompt": "Do you want to proceed with creating this user?"
  },
  "user_data": { "first_name": "Jane", ... }
}
```
> Note: password is NEVER returned in `user_data`.

**Error case (if validation fails):**
```json
{
  "detail": {
    "message": "Validation failed. Fix errors before analysis.",
    "errors": ["Password must contain at least one uppercase letter"]
  }
}
```

---

### `POST /api/users/create`
**Step 3** — Only after human approval. Creates user in AD (or prints in dry run).

**PowerShell test (dry run — safe to run):**
```powershell
$body = @{
    first_name            = "Jane"
    last_name             = "Doe"
    password              = "Welcome@123"
    ou_path               = "OU=IT,DC=company,DC=com"
    email                 = "jane.doe@company.com"
    department            = "IT"
    must_change_password  = $true
    password_never_expires = $false
    account_status        = "enabled"
} | ConvertTo-Json

Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://localhost:8080/api/users/create" `
  -Method POST -ContentType "application/json" -Body $body
```

**Expected response (dry run):**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "[DRY RUN] User 'Jane Doe' would be created successfully at CN=Jane Doe,OU=IT,DC=company,DC=com",
  "user_dn": "CN=Jane Doe,OU=IT,DC=company,DC=com",
  "username": "jane.doe",
  "dry_run": true,
  "details": { "attributes": { "sAMAccountName": "jane.doe", ... } }
}
```

---

## 3. AI Chat Routes

### `POST /api/ai/chat`
Send a message to the Gemini AI assistant.

**PowerShell test:**
```powershell
$body = @{
    messages = @(
        @{ role = "user"; content = "What is a UPN in Active Directory?" }
    )
    current_form_data = $null
} | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5

Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://localhost:8080/api/ai/chat" `
  -Method POST -ContentType "application/json" -Body $body
```

**Expected response:**
```json
{
  "response": "A User Principal Name (UPN) is the username in email format..."
}
```

**Multi-turn chat test:**
```powershell
$body = @{
    messages = @(
        @{ role = "user";      content = "What fields are required?" }
        @{ role = "assistant"; content = "First name, last name, password and OU path are required." }
        @{ role = "user";      content = "What is an OU path?" }
    )
} | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5

Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://localhost:8080/api/ai/chat" `
  -Method POST -ContentType "application/json" -Body $body
```

---

### `GET /api/ai/health`
Check if Gemini AI is configured.

**PowerShell test:**
```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://localhost:8080/api/ai/health" -Method GET
```

**Expected (key configured):**
```json
{
  "ai_configured": true,
  "model": "gemini-2.0-flash-lite",
  "message": "AI ready"
}
```

**Expected (no key):**
```json
{
  "ai_configured": false,
  "model": "gemini-2.0-flash-lite",
  "message": "No GEMINI_API_KEY set — using fallback mode"
}
```

---

